            },
            "answer_text": "If you choose your own prompt, you can write about anything you want. There are numerous theories on what makes a good essay. You can pay college consultants tens of thousands of dollars for their professional advice on how to make your essay stand out and you application get you admitted to an elite college or university. What do you hope to gain by choosing to write a weird essay - show the schools that read you essay that you are weird? Not sure that being weird is a virtue when there are so many earnest young men and women who are trying very hard to craft a narrative that shows the schools they apply to what value they will bring these schools. A college application essay is like a job interview. The school is looking for students who fit their culture, will enhance their student body, raise their ranking, and be stalwart alumni after they graduate. They are not looking for weird characters who would stand out on Halloween night. If by weird, you mean showing how you aren\u2019t the run of a mill college applicant who fits the mean but really isn\u2019t all that inspiring, then sure state your case for why you are an outlier who will fit in with all the other outlier applicants who are trying to gain admission into an elite university or college made up of outlier students. ",
