            "answer_text": "Yes, but make sure it fits in with the prompt.  When I visited UChicago, the Dean of Admissions told a story about a really interesting essay written by a girl, which was about cannibalism. The girl wrote about how if she were forced to eat people, she wouldn't necessarily eat the best tasting people, or the ones with most tender meat. Instead, she wrote, she would want to eat the interesting people, the ones with most unique textures. And, she concluded, that's why she wanted to attend UChicago. She wanted to be with interesting people and be able to experience diverse cultures. She was accepted in to UChicago. ",
