                "name": "Tom Stagliano",
                "href": "/profile/Tom-Stagliano"
            },
            "answer_text": "OK? Forget the word Essay. It is Not an essay. It is an Answer to a question that the college\u2019s admission committee has posed to you and they want to hear \u201cyour voice\u201d through your written words. Pretend you are seated at a table, and across from you are the three admissions officers who will make the major decision to Admit or Reject you. They have read everything else in your application including all letters of recommendation and now they merely want to hear your Answers to a few questions. They are three adults of different ethic background, race, sex, and political philosophy. Now Answer their questions. Period. Only write a Weird answer if you believe you are a Weird person and want to use that to get admitted to that college, because you sense an openness for your weirdness at that college. All the best. ",
