                "name": "Stephen Kahn",
                "href": "/profile/Stephen-Kahn-12"
            },
            "answer_text": "The other answers are excellent. Choose an appropriate school. The weirder the topic, the better your writing must be in terms of grammar, spelling, punctuation, diction, and so on. Also, there is no substitute for good writing. If you are applying to Cat Tech, MIT, etc., write a brilliant essay in computer code that only a genius can decode and get the joke. Something like a new episode of the Big Bang Theory, but a new episode much funnier and surprising. You better be smart too. I went to college over 50 years ago at U California Berkeley, wrote a really clever essay, got in, and flunked out. I eventually graduated somewhere else. So don\u2019t aim for above your level. ",
